item.content:encoded:
Animal Catalog

Koala

Habitats

Koalas (Phascolarctos cinereus) are Australias largest arboreal (tree-dwelling) marsupials. They are also one of Australias most iconic animals.

Koalas are found in inland and coastal areas of eastern Australia, from north-east Queensland to the Eyre Peninsula in South Australia. Victorian koalas have longer and thicker fur than koalas living in Queensland, which is an adaptation to Victorias colder climate.

Diet

Koalas feed almost exclusively on leaves of Eucalyptus trees, which provide a diet that is low in energy. Because of their low energy diet, koalas are sedentary for most of the day and are only active for around four hours, usually after dark.Koalas usually move between trees by walking along the ground, however, they can also jump between trees.

Welcome To

Wild Verve

Learn More

Becoming a Wild Animal Expert in Victoria

Wild Verve Helps you know Victorian wild animal better by providing information on animals nature, possible location, conservation status and local rules. Advice are also given to deal with the situation when you want to have a close interaction with animals

Learn More

Where do they live?

Getting know about the spotting area of the animal can help you find them easier

What are their natures and behaviors?

Some animal are more aggressive than you thought, it is better for you to know more about them

What local rule do I need to abide?

There are rules to interact with wild animals in Victoria, you need to abide by them to aviod harming animals

What Things you Need to Know Before Visiting Our Friends?

Let's Get Started

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: wildverveadmin
item.content:encoded:
About Us

Background

Australian wild animals are adorable; however underestimating them may cause tragedy. Between 2000 and 2010, 254 human deaths were related to animals in Australia. Since more travelers are coming to Australia and wish to have a closer look with local animals, they need to know the rules when getting along with them, and be well-prepared for the potential danger.

Our Goal

Wild Verve provides necessary information of wild animals in Victoria for adult tourists aged between 18 and 35, including possible location details of exotic animals in Victoria, information on the animals nature whether it is docile or aggressive, information on the conservation status of the animal and the rules to abide by given the status and precautionary information on how to deal with the situation when encountering a wild animal that could potentially be agitated

Team Four-Tified
